  "input_214_description": "<p>Kiwango cha juu cha ardhi kinachopatikana kwa upandaji miti/upandaji miti.</p><p class=\"sources-header\">Vyanzo:&nbsp;</p><ul>\n<li>The Royal Society &amp; Royal Academy of Engineering. (2018). <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://royalsociety.org/-/media/policy/projects/greenhouse-gas-removal/royal-society-greenhouse-gas-removal-report-2018.pdf/\"><i>Greenhouse gas removal.</i></a> p. 67 Table 2.</li>\n<li>Mo, L., et al. (2023). <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-06723-z\">Integrated global assessment of the natural forest carbon potential.</a> <i>Nature, 624</i>(7990), 92-101.</li>\n<li>Walker, W. S., et al. (2022). <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.2111312119\">The global potential for increased storage of carbon on land.</a> <i>Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 119</i>(23).</li>\n<li>Erb, K.-H., et al. (2018). <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.1038/nature25138\">Unexpectedly large impact of forest management and grazing on global vegetation biomass.</a> <i>Nature, 553</i>(7686), 73-76.</li>\n<li>Bastin, J.-F., et al. (2019). <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.1126/science.aax0848\">The Global Tree Restoration Potential.</a> <i>Science, 365</i>(6448), 76–79.</li>\n<li>Russell, M. (2020). <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://rss.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/1740-9713.01461\"><i>Do forests have the capacity for 1 trillion extra trees?</i></a> Significance, 17(6). 8-9.</li>\n</ul>",
